div><div>ILVE KGSET001 Total Extension Glide Racks</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>168.00</bdi></span></a></div></div> </div> </div> </div> \", \"Option1 Name\": \"Color\", \"Option1 Value\": \"Glossy Black\", \"Option2 Name\": \"Trim\", \"Option2 Value\": \"Brass\", \"Option3 Name\": \"Oven Door Type\", \"Option3 Value\": \"Triple Glass Door\"}, {\"Variant Name\": \"ILVE - 30 inch Majestic II Induction Range (Glossy Black / Copper / Triple Glass Door) - UMI30NE3BKP\", \"Variant SKU\": \"UMI30NE3BKP\", \"Variant Image\": \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820-3.jpg\", \"Variant All Images\": [\"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820_168260-4.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820_168261-4.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820_168262-4.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820_10640-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820_168554-4.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820_10641-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820_10642-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30NE3BKP_p12820_10643-3.jpg\"], \"Variant Price\": \"7990.00\", \"Variant Barcode\": \"8051202194068\", \"Variant URLS\": \"\", \"Variant Count\": \"\", \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>The Majestic 30 induction range is a perfect example of how traditional Italian design can coexist with modern technology. It has four efficient element zones, a total oven capacity of four cubic feet, a 4.3-inch full-touch control display, and an enamel oven cavity that is easy to clean.</p><p>Product Status: Available</p><div><p><strong>Majestic</strong></p><p>The show-stopping range cooker that will turn your kitchen into a showpiece.</p><p></p><p>With its rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, solutions, and technologies derived from the world of professional cooking, Majestic is a freestanding statement-piece that effortlessly blends into any setting while still commanding attention. It is a true master of form and function.</p><p></p><p>The sculpted, meticulously detailed forms of majestic range cookers, crafted from pure steel, make them eye-catching kitchen appliances that also serve as decorative accents.</p><p></p><p>These are the real deal, hand-picked gems of professional design for your home kitchen. They come in a variety of sizes (from 30 to 60 inches) and offer a plethora of set-up options, as well as RAL Classic shades upon request and fine metallic finishes.</p><p></p><ul><li>Detector of remaining heat</li><li>Timer with built-in self-exclusion</li><li>Control of bridges</li><li>Function that boosts</li><li>Controls that slide</li><li>Preventing harm to children</li><li>Widescreen 4.3-inch</li><li>Fire safety and prevention of overheating</li><li>Electronic temperature control with pinpoint accuracy</li><li>A brief introduction</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Technology for Products</strong></p><p></p><p>Not only is aesthetics important, but having the best technologies available is essential for cooking well and enjoying oneself. ILVE puts its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that guarantee the best satisfaction by combining top-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies for the Kitchen Range</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Induction Range (Oven)</strong></p><p>With their modern technology and elegant design, Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) make cooking a breeze. Induction offers many benefits, such as safe cooking, reduced energy consumption, safety, adjustable temperature control, and quick cooking times, all of which make it easier to prepare dishes and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measurement of Persistent Heat</strong></p><p>Wear protective gloves and avoid touching or setting anything delicate on the glass because it is hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>Timer with Built-In Stop Function</strong></p><p>Once the specified time has passed, the active zone is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Bridge Management</strong></p><p>With this function, induction cooktops (hobs) allow you to control two adjacent zones with one command, as if they were one big zone.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhancement Role</strong></p><p>Makes it possible to concentrate the entire induction burner's power on a specific area, allowing you to boil and cook food more quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Handles</strong></p><p>For instance, by gliding your finger from right to left or vice versa, you can adjust the operating temperature using this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Child Protection</strong></p><p>The induction cooktop (hob) cannot be turned on using the controls once this feature has been enabled and will remain so until disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Prevention of Overheating and Liquid Spills</strong></p><p>A safety feature will activate and turn off the stovetop (hob) in the event of an overheat or liquid spill.</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>The Oven Guys</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Ovens: Massive Capacity and Peak Efficiency.</strong></p><p>Our 30-inch range offers a maximum oven capacity of 4 cubic feet, so you can choose between a single or double combination oven to accommodate even the largest of dishes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Accurate Electronic Regulation of Temperature</strong></p><p>In contrast to traditional ovens, which experience temperature fluctuations, the electronic control keeps the oven temperature constant the whole time.</p><p></p><p><strong>Full-Screen 4.3-Inch Display</strong></p><p>The display guarantees excellent readability with TFT technology, showing every function with clear and immediate graphics.</p><p></p><p><strong>Our TFT display is designed to be user-friendly, comprehensive, and high resolution.</strong></p><p>With a single touch of the big screen, you can control all the features of either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously. You can set the temperature, set the timer, and program the ovens to start and stop cooking automatically.</p><p></p><p><strong>Comfortably Closing Door System</strong></p><p>A shock absorber is integrated into the door hinges, allowing for a quieter and more gradual closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Food Preparation Assessment Tool</strong></p><p>A must-have tool for taking internal temperatures, such as those of meat slices.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection (Hot Food Preparation)</strong></p><p>You can achieve a crispy baked dish or a soft and juicy roast thanks to this system, which removes the vapors from inside the cavity, allowing you to choose a drier or more moist cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Within the temperature range of 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>No matter how complicated or intricate your recipe is, an ILVE oven can effortlessly and perfectly complete every step, from proofing to cooking, roasting to low temperature.</p><p></p><p><strong>Using High Density Insulation and Tangential Cooling Ventilation</strong></p><p>Ensures that the kitchen and its adjacent furniture do not become too hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>The Ultimate Cleaning Solution: A Folding Grill Coil</strong></p><p>You can clean the top part of the cavity more easily thanks to the articulated support, which allows you to lower the electric heating element of the grill.</p><p></p><p><strong>Dishwasher Safe Enamel</strong></p><p>Because the grease doesn't adhere to the surface, it's easier to clean.</p><p></p><p><strong>Baked Goods. UOV 76 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Pizza party</li><li>Removing From Freeze</li><li>Prolonged cooking</li><li>Getting started quickly</li><li>Extensive cooking with moisture</li><li>Cooking with a fan grill</li><li>Grilling in a covered area</li><li>Making food from on high</li><li>Steaming food cooked in the air</li><li>Using the ground up</li><li>Using moisture from below</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Normal cooking with moist static heat</li><li>Numerous fan-assisted cooking methods</li><li>Several wet fan ovens</li><li>Green food preparation</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Party Pizza</strong></p><p>The lower heating element, in conjunction with the other, less powerful heating elements, produces the ideal temperature and baking conditions for pizza, bread, and focaccia.</p><p></p><p><strong>Warming up</strong></p><p>Ensures that any food that is frozen will defrost rapidly, bringing it to room temperature without changing its flavor or appearance.</p><p></p><p><strong>Extensive Preparation</strong></p><p>For foods that require a crispy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc., this steam-discharge method guarantees rapid and intense cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Rapid Start</strong></p><p>With the fast preheating function, you can quickly get to the temperature you want, and then select the cooking mode that's going to work best with your food. What's more, when set to a low temperature, it can also function as rapid defrosting.</p><p></p><p><strong>Extremely Wet Cooking</strong></p><p>Its steam block ensures rapid and intense cooking and is ideal for moist foods such as braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, and chicken cacciatore.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grilling with a Fan</strong></p><p>Many foods, including sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, etc., can be cooked quickly and thoroughly with this function, which also significantly reduces energy consumption.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enclosure for Grilling</strong></p><p>Ideal for searing fillets, Florentine steaks, fish, and even veggies quickly and thoroughly, as well as browning and roasting meat in general.</p><p></p><p><strong>Elevated Cooking</strong></p><p>Burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc., all benefit from browning and the finishing touch of color that this function provides.</p><p></p><p><strong>Healthy Recipes from Above</strong></p><p>Excellent for browning and finishing the color of a wide variety of foods without mushiness.</p><p></p><p><strong>Lessons in Home Cooking</strong></p><p>Pastries (such as biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, and so on) are best cooked in this way to finish the cooking cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>In-Depth Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>In order to finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture, this is the best way to do it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Regular Static Cooking</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, etc. are all great candidates for this electric oven's classic function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Wet Static Regular Cooking</strong></p><p>Standard static cooking gets even more wet with this.</p><p></p><p><strong>Multi-Fan Oven Utilization</strong></p><p>You can bake a variety of foods at once without worrying about their aromas blending\\u2014lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc.\\u2014and save both time and energy thanks to this feature.</p><p></p><p><strong>Fan Cooking with Multiple Moist Fans</strong></p><p>This makes regular cooking with multiple fans even more moist.</p><p></p><p><strong>Natural Food Preparation</strong></p><p>Slow roasting foods, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, and delicate pastries, necessitate longer cooking times when using the ECO function, which significantly reduces power consumption. However, this cooking cycle is not meant for foods that are frozen.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measure 65 in California</strong></p><p>Caution: Danger to Health and Fertility</p><p><strong><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Check out this website: www.P65Warnings.ca.gov.</a></strong></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">Sorry, but the video tag isn't compatible with your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/wKi6ZYNcCxY.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/re1Uo4qdmcc.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/4JuPNm3uQqU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> </div></div><br/><br/><strong>Freight Charges May Apply</strong><br/><br/></div></div> </div> <h3 class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtitle\\\"><span aria-controls=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_features\\\" aria-selected=\\\"false\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tab\\\" data-slug=\\\"features\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tab_features\\\" role=\\\"tab\\\" tabindex=\\\"-1\\\"> <span class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtext\\\">Features</span> </span></h3> <div a