001 Total Extension Glide Racks</div><span><bdi><span>$</span>168.00</bdi></span></a></div></div> </div> </div> </div> \", \"Option1 Name\": \"Color\", \"Option1 Value\": \"Blue Grey\", \"Option2 Name\": \"Trim\", \"Option2 Value\": \"Brass\", \"Option3 Name\": \"Oven Door Type\", \"Option3 Value\": \"Solid Door\"}, {\"Variant Name\": \"ILVE - 30 inch Majestic II Induction Range (Blue Grey / Copper / Solid Door) - UMI30QNE3BGP\", \"Variant SKU\": \"UMI30QNE3BGP\", \"Variant Image\": \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789-2.jpg\", \"Variant All Images\": [\"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789-2.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789_168598-3.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789_168599-3.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789_168600-3.webp\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789_169178-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789_169179-3.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789_10785-2.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789_10786-2.jpg\", \"https://us.ilve.com/wp-content/uploads/UMI30QNE3BGP_p12789_10787-2.jpg\"], \"Variant Price\": \"8690.00\", \"Variant Barcode\": \"8051202237376\", \"Variant URLS\": \"\", \"Variant Count\": \"\", \"Variant HTML\": \" <div aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\" aria-labelledby=\\\"station-tabs-tab_description\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel station-tabs-default-tabpanel\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_description\\\" role=\\\"tabpanel\\\"> <div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><div class=\\\"station-tabs-tabcontent\\\"><p>Featuring a 4.3-inch full-touch oven control display, an easy-clean enamel oven cavity, four precise and efficient element zones, and a total oven capacity of four cubic feet, the Majestic 30-inch induction range combines traditional Italian design with state-of-the-art technology.</p><p>Availability: 90 - 120 days for pre-order</p><div><p><strong>Majestic</strong></p><p>The show-stopping range cooker that will turn your kitchen into a showpiece.</p><p></p><p>Majestic is a freestanding statement-piece that exudes elegance and functionality in equal measure. Its design draws inspiration from the world of professional cooking and features rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, and solutions and technologies. Despite its ability to blend into any setting, Majestic commands attention.</p><p></p><p>The sculpted, meticulously detailed forms of majestic range cookers, crafted from pure steel, make them eye-catching kitchen appliances that also serve as decorative accents.</p><p></p><p>They are masterpieces of craftsmanship, crafted for your home's kitchen. They come in a variety of colors, including RAL Classic shades upon request, and are complemented by fine metallic finishes. They are available in a wide range of sizes, from 30 to 60 inches, and provide multiple options for installation.</p><p></p><ul><li>Detector of remaining heat</li><li>Automatically stops the timer</li><li>Bridge management</li><li>Enhancement feature</li><li>Controls that slide</li><li>Protecting children</li><li>Retina 4.3-inch touchscreen</li><li>Fire safety and prevention of overheating</li><li>Accurate electronic regulation of temperature</li><li>Getting started quickly</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Technology for Products</strong></p><p></p><p>When it comes to cooking, form follows function. ILVE puts its knowledge and expertise to work for you, providing solutions that combine high-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness, ensuring the highest level of satisfaction at all times.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies for the Kitchen Stove</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Dual-Platform Induction Cooktop</strong></p><p>Using cutting-edge technology in a stylish and elegant design, Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) expedite the cooking process while minimizing the risk of burns and other food hazards. Induction also helps with cleaning, energy savings, safety, temperature control, and cooking speed, all of which are important when it comes to preparing meals and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Calculator for Remaining Heat</strong></p><p>Wear protective gloves and avoid touching or setting anything delicate on the glass because it is hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>Automatically Stops the Timer</strong></p><p>At the end of the specified time, the active zone is disabled.</p><p></p><p><strong>Control of Bridges</strong></p><p>If your induction cooktop (hob) has this capability, you can treat two adjacent zones as one and use a single command to control them both.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhanced Capability</strong></p><p>Makes it possible to concentrate the entire induction burner's power on a specific area, allowing you to boil and cook food more quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Handles</strong></p><p>For instance, you can adjust the operating temperature simply by gliding your finger from right to left or left to right thanks to this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Ensuring Safety for Children</strong></p><p>After you enable this feature, you can't use the controls to turn on the induction cooktop (hob).</p><p></p><p><strong>Limiting Heat and Preventing Liquid Spills</strong></p><p>A safety device will trip and turn off the stovetop (hob) in the event of an overheat or liquid spill.</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>The Oven Guys</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Impressive Size and Power: The Ovens.</strong></p><p>Our 30-inch range offers a maximum oven capacity of 4 cubic feet, so you can choose between a single or double combination oven to accommodate even the largest of dishes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Electronic Temperature Control with High Precision</strong></p><p>The oven's temperature stays consistent throughout thanks to the electronic control, unlike with traditional ovens.</p><p></p><p><strong>Full-Screen 4.3-Inch Display</strong></p><p>With TFT technology, the screen guarantees excellent legibility, showing quick and clear graphics for every function.</p><p></p><p><strong>TFT Screen; Easy to Use, Extensive, and High-Resolution.</strong></p><p>All the controls for the oven, including temperature, timer, and automatic start/end programming, are conveniently located on the large display, so all you need is a single finger to operate either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously.</p><p></p><p><strong>Door with a System for Soft Closing</strong></p><p>A shock absorber is integrated into the door hinges, allowing for a quieter and more gradual closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Food Preparation Assessment Tool</strong></p><p>The tool you need to check the internal temperature of meat, among other things.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection (Hot Food Preparation)</strong></p><p>You can achieve a crispy baked dish or a soft and juicy roast thanks to this system, which removes the vapors from inside the cavity, allowing you to choose a drier or more moist cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Heat range: 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>No matter how complicated or intricate your recipe is, an ILVE oven can effortlessly and perfectly complete every step, from proofing to cooking, roasting to low temperature.</p><p></p><p><strong>Airflow for Tangential Cooling and High-Density Insulation</strong></p><p>Ensures that the kitchen and its adjacent furniture do not become too hot.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grill Coil that Folds for Easy Cleaning</strong></p><p>The electric heating element of the grill can be lowered for easier cleaning of the top part of the cavity, thanks to the articulated support.</p><p></p><p><strong>Rinse-Free Enamel</strong></p><p>The grease slides off the surface and is easier to wipe off.</p><p></p><p><strong>Using the Oven: UOV 76 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>The pizza party</li><li>Removing from Freeze</li><li>Very intense cooking</li><li>Getting started with little</li><li>Extensive cooking with moisture</li><li>Grilling with a fan</li><li>Grilling in a covered area</li><li>Making food from on high</li><li>Steaming food cooked in the air</li><li>An Underground Kitchen</li><li>Cooking with moisture from below</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Cooking that is moist and static</li><li>Numerous fan-assisted cooking methods</li><li>Several wet fan ovens</li><li>Sustainable cuisine</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Party Pizza</strong></p><p>This oven is perfect for baking pizza, bread, focaccia, and other similar foods. The lower heating element is the primary heat source, and it works in tandem with the other, less powerful heating elements to provide the ideal conditions for baking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Removing from Freeze</strong></p><p>Ensures that any food that is frozen will defrost rapidly, bringing it to room temperature without changing its flavor or appearance.</p><p></p><p><strong>Extensive Preparation</strong></p><p>For foods that require a crispy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc., this steam-discharge method guarantees rapid and intense cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Easy Beginning</strong></p><p>With the fast preheating function, you can quickly get to the temperature you want, and then select the cooking mode that's going to work best with your food. What's more, when set to a low temperature, it can also function as rapid defrosting.</p><p></p><p><strong>Thoroughly Moist Cooking</strong></p><p>Its steam block ensures rapid and intense cooking and is ideal for moist foods such as braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, and chicken cacciatore.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grilling with a Fan</strong></p><p>This function is great for a wide variety of foods because it is quick, deep, and uses a lot of energy. Some examples of these foods are sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, and pork chops.</p><p></p><p><strong>Grilling under Covered Spaces</strong></p><p>Functions such as quick and deep grilling, browning, roasting, and cooking fillets, Florentine steaks, fish, and vegetables are highly recommended.</p><p></p><p><strong>Above-Ground Cooking</strong></p><p>This function is perfect for browning and finishing a wide variety of foods; burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc. all benefit from it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Healthy Recipes from Above</strong></p><p>Great for browning and giving a variety of foods that last splash of color a little more color without making them tough.</p><p></p><p><strong>Lessons in Home Cooking</strong></p><p>When cooking pastries (such as biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, etc.), this is the best way to finish the cooking cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>In-Depth Recipes for Moist Food</strong></p><p>In order to finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture, this is the best way to do it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Regular, Unchanging Cooking</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, etc. are all great candidates for this electric oven's classic function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Normal Cooking with Moist Static</strong></p><p>Standard static cooking gets even more wet with this.</p><p></p><p><strong>Multi-Fan Oven Utilization</strong></p><p>Lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc. can all be baked at the same time without blending aromas thanks to this feature, which also helps to save power and time.</p><p></p><p><strong>Fan Cooking with Multiple Moist Fans</strong></p><p>This increases the amount of moisture in a standard multi-fan oven.</p><p></p><p><strong>Eco-Friendly Food Preparation</strong></p><p>Slow roasting foods, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, and delicate pastries, necessitate longer cooking times when using the ECO function, which significantly reduces power consumption. However, this cooking cycle is not meant for foods that are frozen.</p><p></p><p><strong>Proposition 65 in California\\u2014</strong></p><p>Health Risks: Cancer and Fertility Impairment</p><p><strong><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Visit www.P65Warnings.ca.gov for more regulations in your state.</a></strong></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">Sorry, but the video tag isn't compatible with your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">There is a problem with the video tag in your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/wKi6ZYNcCxY.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/re1Uo4qdmcc.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">Sorry, but the video tag isn't compatible with your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/4JuPNm3uQqU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> </div></div><br/><br/><strong>Freight Charges May Apply</strong><br/><br/></div></div> </div> <h3 class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtitle\\\"><span aria-controls=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_features\\\" aria-selected=\\\"false\\\" class=\\\"station-tabs-tab\\\" data-slug=\\\"features\\\" id=\\\"station-tabs-tab_features\\\" role=\\\"ta