ian design can coexist with modern technology. It has four efficient element zones, a total oven capacity of four cubic feet, a 4.3-inch full-touch control display, and an enamel oven cavity that is easy to clean.</p><p>Order now for delivery in 90 to 120 days!</p><div><p><strong>Majestic</strong></p><p>This show-stopping range cooker will be the focal point of your kitchen.</p><p></p><p>With its rounded lines, crafted details, fine finishes, solutions, and technologies derived from the world of professional cooking, Majestic is a freestanding statement-piece that effortlessly blends into any setting while still commanding attention. It is a masterful embodiment of the ultimate range cooker, combining form and function.</p><p></p><p>The graceful curves and meticulously crafted details of majestic range cookers make them beautiful additions to any home.</p><p></p><p>Designed for your home's kitchen, these workhorses are available in a variety of colors (from 30 to 60 inches) and set-up options (from multiple options) and can be customized to RAL Classic shades upon request. They also feature fine metallic finishes.</p><p></p><ul><li>Indictor for residual heat</li><li>Timer with built-in self-exclusion</li><li>Control of bridges</li><li>Booster role</li><li>Handles for sliding</li><li>Ensuring children's safety</li><li>Retina 4.3-inch touchscreen</li><li>Fire safety and prevention of overheating</li><li>Electronic temperature control with pinpoint accuracy</li><li>Fast start</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>Technology for Products</strong></p><p></p><p>Not only is aesthetics important, but having the best technologies available is essential for cooking well and enjoying oneself. ILVE puts its research and experience to work for you, providing solutions that combine top-level performance with maximum simplicity, safety, and user-friendliness, guaranteeing the best satisfaction at all times.</p><p></p><p><strong>Technologies for the Kitchen Range</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Induction Range (Oven)</strong></p><p>Majestic induction cooktops (hobs) are a modern, practical, and safe method of cooking that combines cutting-edge technology with an elegant and modern aesthetic. Induction offers many benefits, such as safety, ease of cleaning, energy savings, and versatile temperature control and cooking speed, all of which make it easier to prepare dishes and recipes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Determinant of Remaining Heat</strong></p><p>The glass is hot, so be careful not to touch it or put anything on it; doing so could cause damage.</p><p></p><p><strong>Stop-Starting Timer</strong></p><p>Activates the active zone until the timer goes off.</p><p></p><p><strong>Control of Bridges</strong></p><p>This feature allows you to control two adjacent zones on induction cooktops (hobs) with one command, as if they were one large zone.</p><p></p><p><strong>Enhancement Role</strong></p><p>Makes it possible to concentrate the entire induction burner's power on a specific area, allowing you to boil and cook food more quickly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Slide Management</strong></p><p>For instance, you can adjust the operating temperature simply by gliding your finger from right to left or left to right thanks to this convenient \\\"touch control\\\" system.</p><p></p><p><strong>Child Protection</strong></p><p>After you enable this feature, you can't use the controls to turn on the induction cooktop (hob).</p><p></p><p><strong>Keeping Things From Overheating and Leaking Liquids</strong></p><p>A safety feature will activate and turn off the stovetop (hob) in the event of an overheat or liquid spill.</p><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>The Oven Guys</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>The Massive and Efficient Ovens.</strong></p><p>Our 30-inch range offers a maximum oven capacity of 4 cubic feet, so you can choose between a single or double combination oven to accommodate even the largest of dishes.</p><p></p><p><strong>Controlling Temperature with Electronic Precision</strong></p><p>The electronic control keeps the oven temperature steady, unlike regular ovens, so it doesn't change during the cooking process.</p><p></p><p><strong>A 4.3-inch Full-Touch Screen</strong></p><p>With TFT technology, the screen guarantees excellent legibility, showing quick and clear graphics for every function.</p><p></p><p><strong>TFT Screen; Easy to Use, Extensive, and High-Resolution.</strong></p><p>All the controls for the oven, including temperature, timer, and automatic start/end programming, are conveniently located on the large display, so all you need is a single finger to operate either the single oven or both ovens simultaneously.</p><p></p><p><strong>Door with a System for Soft Closing</strong></p><p>A shock absorber is integrated into the door hinges, allowing for a quieter and more gradual closing.</p><p></p><p><strong>Food Preparation Assessment Tool</strong></p><p>The tool you need to check the internal temperature of meat, among other things.</p><p></p><p><strong>Steam Ejection for Wet Cooking</strong></p><p>If you want a crispy baked dish or a juicy roast, this system will remove the vapours from inside the cavity, giving you the option to cook it dry or wet.</p><p></p><p><strong>Heat range: 85 to 575 degrees Fahrenheit</strong></p><p>You can effortlessly and perfectly prepare even the most intricate and sophisticated recipes in an ILVE oven, whether you're proofing, cooking, roasting, or using low heat.</p><p></p><p><strong>Using High Density Insulation and Tangential Cooling Ventilation</strong></p><p>Shields kitchen and oven-related furniture from dangerously high temperatures.</p><p></p><p><strong>A Convenient Way to Clean Your Grill Every Time</strong></p><p>The electric heating element of the grill can be lowered for easier cleaning of the top part of the cavity, thanks to the articulated support.</p><p></p><p><strong>Dishwasher Safe Enamel</strong></p><p>Because the grease doesn't adhere to the surface, it's easier to clean.</p><p></p><p><strong>Baking Processes. UOV 76 E3 TFT S</strong></p><p></p><ul><li>Pizza party</li><li>Removing from Freeze</li><li>Prolonged cooking</li><li>A brief introduction</li><li>Extensive cooking with moisture</li><li>The cooking method of the fan grill</li><li>Cooking on the grill with the door closed</li><li>Making food from on high</li><li>Steaming food cooked in the air</li><li>Recipes viewed from below</li><li>Cooking with moisture from below</li><li>Regular, static cooking</li><li>Static, moist, typical cooking</li><li>Using multiple fan cooking options</li><li>Several wet fan ovens</li><li>Sustainable cuisine</li></ul><p></p><hr/><p></p><p><strong>A Pizza Party</strong></p><p>Perfect for baking pizza, bread, and focaccia. The lower heating element is the primary heat source, and with the assistance of the other, less powerful heating elements, it produces the ideal conditions for this kind of cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Removing from Freeze</strong></p><p>It guarantees that any food that is frozen will defrost rapidly, bringing it to room temperature without changing its flavor or appearance.</p><p></p><p><strong>Cooking to the Extremes</strong></p><p>For foods that require a crispy finish, such as baked potatoes and veggies, chicken, salt-crusted fish, etc., this steam-discharge method guarantees rapid and intense cooking.</p><p></p><p><strong>Easy Beginning</strong></p><p>With the fast preheating function, you can quickly get to the temperature you want, and then select the cooking mode that's going to work best with your food. What's more, when set to a low temperature, it can also function as rapid defrosting.</p><p></p><p><strong>Thoroughly Moist Cooking</strong></p><p>Its steam block ensures rapid and intense cooking and is ideal for moist foods such as braised meat, stewed rabbit, salt cod, and chicken cacciatore.</p><p></p><p><strong>Searing on a Fan Grill</strong></p><p>Many foods, including sausages, pork or mixed kebabs, game, Roman-style gnocchi, etc., can be cooked quickly and thoroughly with this function, which also significantly reduces energy consumption.</p><p></p><p><strong>Methods for Grilling with a Closed Door</strong></p><p>This grilling function is ideal for browning and roasting meat, fish, vegetables, fillets, Florentine steak, and other types of meat quickly and thoroughly.</p><p></p><p><strong>Recipes from the Sky</strong></p><p>This function is perfect for browning and finishing a wide variety of foods; burgers, pork chops, veal steaks, sole, cuttlefish, etc. all benefit from it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Heavenly, Moist Recipes</strong></p><p>Great for browning and giving a variety of foods that last splash of color a little more color without making them tough.</p><p></p><p><strong>Lessons in Home Cooking</strong></p><p>For pastries (biscuits, meringues, leavened desserts, fruit desserts, etc.), this is the best way to finish cooking the cycle.</p><p></p><p><strong>Healthy Recipes Made from Scratch</strong></p><p>In order to finish the cooking cycle with the correct amount of moisture, this is the best way to do it.</p><p></p><p><strong>Normal Static Cooking</strong></p><p>Pork chops, sausages, salt cod, braised meat, game, roast veal, meringues, biscuits, baked fruit, etc. are all great candidates for this electric oven's classic function.</p><p></p><p><strong>Dry Static Regular Cooking</strong></p><p>Standard static cooking gets even more wet with this.</p><p></p><p><strong>Multi-Fan Oven Utilization</strong></p><p>You can bake a variety of foods at once without worrying about their aromas blending\\u2014lasagna, croissants and brioches, tarts, cakes, etc.\\u2014and save both time and energy thanks to this feature.</p><p></p><p><strong>Fan Cooking with Multiple Moist Fans</strong></p><p>This increases the amount of moisture in a standard multi-fan oven.</p><p></p><p><strong>eco-friendly food preparation</strong></p><p>With the ECO function, cooking times adapt to slow roasting, like braised meats, white meats, baked pasta, delicate pastries, and so on. This cooking cycle is not meant for frozen foods, but it does allow for significant savings on electricity consumption.</p><p></p><p><strong>Measure 65 in California</strong></p><p>CAUTION: Potential Cancer and Reproductive Risks</p><p><strong><a href=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/.\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Visit www.P65Warnings.ca.gov for more regulations in your state.</a></strong></p></div> <div><div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/qIZ8MSDCu-Y.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/RRQlYvQPAMg.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/Uh_EEzfUhUU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/wKi6ZYNcCxY.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/re1Uo4qdmcc.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">Sorry, but the video tag isn't compatible with your browser.</video> </div> <div> <video controls=\\\"\\\" preload=\\\"auto\\\" src=\\\"/cdn/shop/files/4JuPNm3uQqU.mp4\\\" style=\\\"max-width:320px; margin-bottom:1.2rem;\\\">The video tag is not supported by your browser.</video> </div> </div></div><br/><br/><strong>Freight Charges May Apply</strong><br/><br/></div></div> </div> <h3 class=\\\"station-tabs-tabtitle\\\"><span aria-controls=\\\"station-tabs-tabpanel_features\\\" aria-selected=\\\"false\\\"